In ruby, you can access only public methods from outside the class.
What if you want to mutate class for only a certain object. Maybe,
you also want access to its instance variables and private methods.
Welcome to instance_eval.

object.instance_eval{snippet}

Inside the code block, it's like you are inside object's class. You
can call instance_variables, private methods, declare new methods.
Thus, mutating class for that specific object.
